milestones.description: Constant has broken the record for officiating the most ODIs (11) as an umpire, going past Dickie Bird
England's 20-run win against New Zealand is the smallest margin of victory in terms of runs in ODIs, beating 80-run win against New Zealand
Bevan Congdon and Lance Cairns's 68-run partnership is the highest for the 8th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 55 between Derek Randall and Robin Jackman
Bevan Congdon and Lance Cairns's 68-run partnership is NZ's highest for the 8th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 48 between Dayle Hadlee and McKechnie
